<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section version="5.0"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
    xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mth="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
    xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xml:id="create_data_element">
    <title>Create or edit a
        d<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T101140+0200" comment="At next revision:
Find out who does this? Admin? Implementer? User? " flag="done"?>ata<?oxy_comment_end?>
        element</title>
    <para>
        <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata width="80%" align="center"
                        fileref="resources/images/maintainence/create_data_element.png" format="PNG"
                    />
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </screenshot>
    </para>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                    role="bold">Data elements</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Data
                    element</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click the add
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T112410+0200" comment="Do not refer to the FAB as an icon, according to MS Manual of Style." flag="done"?>button<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis> field, define the precise name of the
                data element.</para>
            <para>Each data element must have a unique name.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Short name</emphasis> field, define a short name for
                the data element.</para>
            <para>Typically, the short name is an abbreviation of the full data element name. This
                attribute is often used in reports to display the name of the data element, where
                space is limited.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) In the <emphasis role="bold">Code</emphasis> field, assign a
                code.</para>
            <para>In many countries data elements are assigned a code.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Description</emphasis> field, type a description of
                the data element. Be as precise as possible and include complete information about
                how the data element is measured and what its purpose is.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T113601+0200" comment="At next revision:
Is this optional? Recommended?" flag="done"?><emphasis
                    role="bold">Form name</emphasis><?oxy_comment_end?> field, type an alternative
                name of the data element. This name can be used in either section or automatic data
                entry forms. The form name is applied automatically.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Domain
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T113840+0200" comment="Ask SME to use all lower case in GUI." flag="done"?>type<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>
                field, select whether the data element is an aggregate or tracker
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T113726+0200" comment="How do you know which type the data element is?" flag="done"?>type<?oxy_comment_end?>
                of data element.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Value
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T113850+0200" comment="Ask SME to use all lower case in GUI." flag="done"?>type<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>
                field, select the type of data that the data element will record.</para>
            <table frame="all">
                <title>Value
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160926T171237+0200" comment="Table also used in tracker entity attributes."?>types<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.17*"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Value type</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160926T170946+0200" comment="Before release: add missing descriptions"?>Description<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Age</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Coordinate</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>A point coordinate specified as longitude and latitude in
                                    decimal degrees. All coordinate should be specified in the
                                    format &quot;-19.23 , 56.42&quot; with a comma separating the
                                    longitude and latitude.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Date</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Dates rendered as calendar widget in data entry.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Date &amp; time</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Email</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Email.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>File</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>A file resource where you can store external files, for
                                    example documents and photos.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Integer</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Any whole number (positive and negative), including
                                    zero.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Letter</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>A single letter.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Long text</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Textual value. Renders as text area with no length constraint
                                    in forms.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Negative integer</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Any whole number less than (but not including) zero.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Number</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Any real numeric value with a single decimal point. Thousands
                                    separators and scientific notation is not supported.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Percentage</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Whole numbers inclusive between 0 and 100.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Phone number</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Phone number.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Positive integer</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Any whole number greater than (but not including) zero.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Positive of zero integer</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Any positive whole number, including zero.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Organisation unit</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Organisation units rendered as a hierarchy tree widget.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Unit interval</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Any real number greater than or equal to 0 and less than or
                                    equal to 1.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Text</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Textual value. The maximum number of allowed characters per
                                    value is 50,000.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Time</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Time is stored in HH:mm format.</para>
                                <para>HH is a number between 0 and 23</para>
                                <para>mm is a number between 00 and 59</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Tracker associate</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Tracked entity instance. Rendered as dialog with a list of
                                    tracked entity instances and a search field.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Username</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>DHIS 2 user. Rendered as a dialog with a list of users and a
                                    search field.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Yes/No</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Boolean values, renders as drop-down lists in data
                                    entry.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Yes only</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>True values, renders as check-boxes in data entry.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Aggregation type</emphasis> field, select the default
                aggregation operation that will be used on the data element.</para>
            <para>Most data elements should have the <emphasis role="bold">Sum</emphasis> operator.
                This includes all data elements which should be added together. Other data elements,
                such as staffing levels, should be set to use the <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Average</emphasis> operator, when values along the time dimension should not be
                added together, but rather averaged.</para>
            <table frame="all">
                <title>Aggregation
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160926T164524+0200" comment="Before release: add description of all aggregation operator.
Also used for other types of metadata.
For example: tracked entity attribute"?>operators<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Aggregation
                                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T115730+0200" comment="At next revision:
Verify with SME: order or items in list, any special reason?
Probably random, verify with Lars." flag="done"?>operator<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Description</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Average</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Average the values in both the period as and the organisation
                                    unit dimensions.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Average (sum in organisation unit hierarchy)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Average of data values in the period dimension, sum in the
                                    organisation unit
                                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T120035+0200" comment="At next revision:
Verify with SME: correct with org units in plural?
" flag="done"?>dimensions<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Count</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Count of data values.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Min</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Minimum of data values.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Max</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Maximum of data values.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>None</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>No aggregation is performed in any dimension.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Sum</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Sum of data values in the period and organisation unit
                                    dimension.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Standard deviation</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Standard deviation (population-based) of data values.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Variance</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Variance (population-based) of data values.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>If you want to save zeros for a particular reason, select <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Store zero data values</emphasis>. By default, DHIS2 does not store zeros
                entered in the data entry module.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">URL</emphasis> field, enter a
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T134852+0200" comment="Verify with SME:
Always a link?
Mandatory?
Recommended?

Info: Probably dev for a specific use case, not mandatory." flag="done"?>link<?oxy_comment_end?>
                to an in-depth description of the data element.</para>
            <para>For example a link to a metadata repository or registry that contains detailed
                technical information about the definition and measurement of the data element.
            </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Category combination</emphasis> field, define which
                category combination the data element should have. This is also known as the
                &quot;<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T135139+0200" comment="At next revision:
Explain further.
Important info for user? Implementer? Admin?
Where can I find more information about this?" flag="done"?>disaggregation<?oxy_comment_end?>&quot;.
            </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select an <emphasis role="bold"
                    ><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T135221+0200" comment="At next revision:
Find out if this is optional?" flag="done"?>Option<?oxy_comment_end?>
                    set</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>Option sets are predefined lists of options which can be
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T135315+0200" comment="At next revision:
Used in which way?" flag="done"?>used<?oxy_comment_end?>
                in data entry.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select an <emphasis role="bold">Option set for comments</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>Option sets for comments are predefined lists of options which can be used to
                specify standardized comments for data values in data entry.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Assign one or multiple <emphasis role="bold">Legends</emphasis>.</para>
            <para><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T135614+0200" comment="At next revision, add link to GIS app topic." flag="done"?>Legend<?oxy_comment_end?>s
                are used in for example the <emphasis role="bold">GIS</emphasis>
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170117T103527+0100" comment="Also to create cell color in the Pivot Table app - confirm with SME."?>app<?oxy_comment_end?>
                to display certain data elements with certain icons.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Set the <emphasis role="bold"
                    ><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160622T134049+0200" comment="At next revision:
Add link to further reading about aggregation levels.

Original text:
&quot;For more information about aggregation levels, refer to the Reporting chapter i the section on data sources for reporting.&quot;
Couldn&apos;t find this section." flag="done"?>Aggregation<?oxy_comment_end?>
                    levels</emphasis>
                t<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T143116+0200" comment="At next revision, reword passive." flag="done"?>o
                allow the data element to be aggregated at one or more
                levels:<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>In the left pane, select the levels you want to assign to the data
                        element.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click the right arrow to assign the aggregation levels.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T142955+0200" comment="At next revision: 
For SME: Is this information still relevant?
Ask Lars" flag="done"?>
            <para>By default, the aggregation will start at the lowest assigned organisation unit.
                If you for example select "Chiefdom", it means that "Chiefdom", "District", and
                "National" aggregates use "Chiefdom" (the highest aggregation level available) as
                the data source, and PHU data will not be included. PHU data will still be available
                for the PHU level, but not included in aggregations to the levels above.</para>
            <para>If you select both "District" and "Chiefdom", it means that the "District" and
                "National" level aggregates use District data as their source, "Chiefdom" will use
                Chiefdom, and "PHU" will use PHU.</para>
            <?oxy_comment_end?>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>If applicable, enter custom attributes values, for example <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Classification</emphasis> or <emphasis role="bold">Collection
                method</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>
                <note>
                    <para>You create custom attributes in the <emphasis role="bold"
                            >Maintenance</emphasis> app: <emphasis role="bold">Other</emphasis> >
                            <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Attributes</emphasis><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160518T114951+0200" comment="At next revsision, add x-ref here." flag="done"?>.<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
                </note>
            </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>If applicable, select compulsory data element group sets, for example <emphasis
                    role="bold">Main data element group</emphasis> or <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Tracker-based data</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>
                <note>
                    <para>You'll only see data element group sets in this form if you've created
                        them and set them to <emphasis role="bold">Compulsory</emphasis>.</para>
                    <para>You create data element group sets in the <emphasis role="bold"
                            >Maintenance</emphasis> app: <emphasis role="bold">Data
                            element</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Date element group
                            set</emphasis><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160518T114951+0200" comment="At next revsision, add x-ref here." flag="done"?>.<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
                </note>
            </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>    
</section>
